TY  - JOUR
T1  - An Algorithm for Multiobjective Zero-One Linear Programming
AU  - Kiziltan, Gülseren
AU  - Yucaoğlu, Erkut
Y1  - 1983/12/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.12.1444
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.12.1444
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1444
EP  - 1453
VL  - 29
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A branch and bound algorithm is presented which is based on the extension of implicit enumeration techniques to multiobjective zero-one linear programming and which appears to be computationally quite efficient. Domination tests, aiming at identifying paths of the enumeration tree that lead to dominated solutions as high up the tree as possible, are developed. Some computational results are also given.
AB  - A branch and bound algorithm is presented which is based on the extension of implicit enumeration techniques to multiobjective zero-one linear programming and which appears to be computationally quite efficient. Domination tests, aiming at identifying paths of the enumeration tree that lead to dominated solutions as high up the tree as possible, are developed. Some computational results are also given.
